messages.content: ((waffle house time
(**waffle house time**)
"Well, isn't this place quite quaint~?" he asks, mostly himself, looking around the waffle house.
He Ignores The People Staring.
Somnus steps ahead to hold it open, gesturing for him to enter.

"My, what a gentlelady~"
He steps in, holding his hand to his mouth like a girl in one of those old weird romance movies.

"I try my best,"
She trails after him, climbing into a booth.
"So, what *do* you like eating~? I thought your strange diet consisted of ventilated moss?" he asks, sitting down across from her and placing his cheek in his hand.

She nods.
"Typically, but I'm trying to get some variety in my diet. I also eat rats."
She grabs his scarf between two fingers, fidgeting with it.
"...And sweaters."
His scarf yanks itself back, wrapping another layer around him. "I'd truly rather you not. Of course, I will supply of *Morise'* sweaters, but my garments are off limits."

She chuckles, blinking at him.
"Are they?"
"Why of course, my dear~! You don't find as perfectly pristine white as this just *anywhere.*"
"...How much do you spend on scarves, Illuvies? Like, annually?'
"Why, whatever do you mean, Somnus?"
"How many scarves do you own? I try to stay out of your closet."
"This is the only one I own, my dear," he says, bringing a hand up to the scarf and fiddling with it.
"So you just... do you wash it?"
"Of course I do! If I don't, then the little specks of blood and dust that form on it will continue to build and *build* until they're completely noticeable spotches!"
"But it hasn't gotten torn yet? You fuck around so much, I'm surprised it hasn't gotten caught on a nail, or something."
"If it got ripped, it would simply stitch itself back together!"

"Mhm."
She nods, then takes a menu and begins examining it.
"You can eat food, right? If you feel like it?"
He waves his hand up and down, sighing. "I'll have whatever you order, I *can* eat, I simply just don't find it *sanitary.*"

"That's boring as fuck. I'm getting hash browns." 
She waves an employee over in a manner that is only mildly threatening.
"Are onions good?"
He shrugs. "Somnus, I truly do not care."

"Don't be fucking rude. We're at a *very* nice establishment,"
She gestures to the grease-stained tile floor for emphasis.
"Have some class."
"Somnus, I'm being *polite.* You may choose whatever you wish for me."

She squints at him, then turns to the server.
"Hash browns, scattered smothered capped. Please,"
She trills, before turning away to rummage for something in the depths of her cape.
He places his chin in his hands, cooing at here. "What are you searching for, my dear insect friend?"

She takes out a pencil and a handful of assorted crayons, then takes a napkin from the dispenser and sets it on the table with a flourish.
"Doodling on napkins is good diner etiquette,"
She states matter-of-factly.
"It feels appropriate, yeah? Fits the, uh. Aesthetic."
He blinks at her, slow and.. *almost* confused. "....Like.. children?"

"Nonono, it's a refined activity."

"Is it?"
He.. Is this another mind-trick of hers? He could've sworn only children partook in coloring on napkins..

"Well, of course! It's art in it's purest form, completely organic and spontaneous. You should be able to appreciate that."
She scribbles a crude self portrait onto it, presenting it to him.
"This is art."

"..I see.."
He hums, confused. "It's surely *wild,* that I know.."
"Y'know Picasso? The art one?"
"Of course. His art is wild yet contained, a perfect mix of reality and fiction."
"Pussy bitch."

*"This* is art."
She continues jabbing at the napkin, forcing back a smile.
"...You just like the paper being mutilated," he observes, realizing she's doing more jabbing than drawing.

She nods.
"Sometimes beauty is violent."
"The path it takes may be mystical, but then end result.. never exceeds expectations."

"Okay."
She scribbles a little more, then seems to get bored with it, scooting the paper away with her crayon.
"...You should try it."

"..."
He lightly pushes the paper back to her, attempting not to be rude. "I'd.. rather not."

She Looks At Him.
"Coward. Draw a lil' picture on the napkin *right now* or you're a pussy."
"I truly do not care of your negative opinions towards me, friend."
He Looks Back.

Without breaking eye contact, she takes another napkin and sets it on the table in front of him.
"Why, are you nervous? Do you think you're too good to draw a little picture on this napkin?"
"No, I simply do not care for it," he says, this time just straight up Ignoring It.
"Why?"
"I cannot say."

"I thought you were a lover of art, Illuvies. Wouldn't it be good for you to branch out? Explore new mediums?"
She rolls a crayon across the table.
"I believe that scribbling on a napkin like a child does not do too well to prepare you for other art mediums. The napkin is simply too rough, the crayons tear through it easily."

She nods.
"You need to work around the medium. It's a challenge; you have to be delicate enough to leave the paper intact, but decisive enough to leave a mark."
Beside them, someone slips a few dollars into the jukebox. A tinny recording of some hit song from the 70s oozes from the shitty speakers.
"It's fun."
//~~what's new pussycat~~
"...Hm. Maybe for someone with the patience of a Plasma, that is," he comments, taking note of the... lack of patients some creatures have.

"Children have a remarkable amount of patience. And even if they do not, they still find joy in ripping the napkins."

"Mhm. Children do generally seem happy, I think. Maybe ripping up napkins is a good place to find joy."
A server sets a plate of fried potato on the table, and Somnus takes it, maintaining eye contact with Illuvies.
"You should draw a self portrait."
He watches as she takes one, not commenting on how disgustingly greasy it seemed. "I truly would rather not," he begins, "My art is in my performance, not pictures."
"That's rather closed-minded of you, friend. I'm disappointed."
"What can I say? My art belongs on a stage!" he announces, ignoring the people who stared in surprise at the sudden noise.

She chuckles, swiveling her head around to look at the disgruntled customers.
"I think you're just scared you'll be bad at it."
"Somnus, my dear friend, I know your trickery when I hear it. I will not fall for it, you should be aware."
"Trickery? I'm the most trustworthy and straightforward person I know, friend. I've never tricked anyone, in my entire life. Ever."
"A hypocrite who states he hates hypocrites, yet loves himself, is a hypocrite within a hypocrite, my fluttery friend."
"What hypocrisy are you referring to? I think you're just trying to distract from the situation at hand."
"I believe you are attempting reverse psychology on me in an attempt to get me to partake in your silly childish activities."
"I believe you are attempting a diversion in an attempt to make me think you aren't a pussy bitch."

"..."
He leans forward, placing his elbows onto the table and holding his chin on his knuckles.
"You truly to like to patronize me, don't you, my dear?"

She mimics him, cupping her face in her hands, and grins shittily.
"I just want you to express yourself creatively, pal. Playing one note is only entertaining for so long."
"Well, I'm not playing only one note, I am simply playing one *instrument.* And every instrument has a variety of songs to play, dear."
"Maybe so, but it won't hurt to expand your horizons."
"It wouldn't hurt to not, either."

"Wouldn't it?"
She sits back again and starts poking at her hash browns.
"Oh, by the way, Illuvies, did you know that moths don't actually eat clothes?"
"Of course, it's an overexaggerated concept. Though I don't typically pay them any mind in the first place."

"I'd change that, if I were you."
She nibbles at a forkful of potato.
"The larvae can still do quite a bit of damage."
"I am aware. I just know they don't shred through clothes like a bear through a fish carcass."

"Not typically."
She taps a clawed finger on the table idly.
"That can change, though."

He decides to not show emotion towards the other. However, if he did, it would be narrowed eyes.
"I'd rather it not, *Somnus dear.*"

"Is that so, *dear?"*
She represses a delighted cackle, toning it down into a smug smile.
"..You've been quite *hostile* to me as of late, my dear.." he observes, leaning back in his booth. "Why is that?"

She shrugs.
"I'm tired of sitting in the vents, and I have a lot of misplaced aggression, I think. I also think that you should draw on that napkin."
"You are beginning to get on my nerves, my dear," he states, though his tone of voice doesnt seem like it.
"What, am I threatening? Do you feel threatened?"
"You are not terrifying in the slightest, my dear. In fact, you remind me of a moth plush."
She blinks at him, then takes a moment to consider the statement. Moth.... plush. Moth plush? She kinda zones out, staring at the table for a few seconds.
"..." He stays quiet, not seeing any point in interrupting her.. whatever it is.

She shakes her head after a moment, ruffling her fur collar.
"So why are you so pissy about it?"
"I'm certainly not *pissy,* my dear. I simply bear a curiosity in my heart that I would like to satiate."
"A curiosity?"
"Of course."
"Regarding...?"
"Figure it out, dear."

She blinks at him again, perplexed.
"Is it... do you want to know the appeal of drawing on a napkin?"

"...."
He chuckles, laying one hand on top of another on the table.
"My dear, you are *insufferable*."
"And yet you are here."
"Because, you're entertaining."

She seems delighted.
"Oh, *thank* you friend, I think you are entertaining also."
She pulls another napkin out and starts scrabbling patterns onto it in crayon.

"Although my ability may not be in pencil and paper, it is quite entertaining to watch *you* engage in the craft, my friend," he says, placing his chin in his hand as he carefully watches her movements.

"Flattering! I still think you should try."
Her crayon breaks, and she stares at it for a moment before putting it back into her cape and fishing out another one.
"..*Fascinating.* Did you obtain those crayons through the restaurant? Or your cape?"

"It's a secret."
She just has a handful of crayons shoved into her pocket.

"I see.."
He Does Not Look.

She scribbles in silence for a few moments before setting her drawing implement down and Looking At Him.
"...How do I convince you to try drawing on the waffle house napkin?"
"You simply cannot," he shrugs.
"What if I ask nicely? Please?"
"I refuse."
"Why?"
"Because I simply would not like to."
"Why not?"
"Will you continue to ask this even if I give a reason?"
"Mmmmaybe."
"Then I will cease to respond."
"Waitwait- if I stop, would you tell me?"
"Tell you what, dear?"
"Why you're so loathe to do this fun arts and crafts project."
"My dear, even if I *did* participate alongside you, it would not be entertaining to me."
"It *would* be entertaining for *me.* Aren't you a performer?"
"I am. But I perform in shows *much* bigger than simple drawings."

"So it's about feeling superior?"
She munches on another bite of hash browns, making a face. Plasma physiology really wasn't made for this.
"Not entirely.. though," he leans forward again. "Believe what you will.

She tilts her head, thinking.
"I still think you should try, Illuvies. At the very least, it's a new experience."
"You know, your desire for me to indulge in your entertainment fuels me with enough pettiness to continue to say no."

"And *your* pettiness gives *me* more desire for you to indulge in my enterainment."
She gestures with her fork.
"So we are at a stalemate."
"Which means I shall conclude this date," he says without missing a beat, standing up quickly. "It was a pleasure, my friend."

She seems mildly disappointed.
"Lovely seeing you, I can continue my crusade later... you can only stay awake for so long, Illuvies."
"As you always say.. Tatah~" he coos, disappearing in a blur of sparkles.
Venor skids to a stop outside. "Lamia." She presses her face up against the glass. "They have *waffles*."
Lamia presses his head against the window. "Waffles."

embeds.title: Waffle House Index
embeds.description: The Waffle House Index is an informal metric named after the Waffle House restaurant chain and is used by the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to determine the effect of a storm and the likely scale of assistance required for disaster recovery.

Somnus appears behind the waffle house, hidden beside a greasy dumpster and a small pile of old cigarette butts. She wrinkles her nose at it, but it'll do just fine. She tosses Superbia to the ground and waits for her to wake up, picking up a cinderblock and crouching beside her.
After a while, Superbia's eyes slowly open. She felt... Dizzy... Her head was hurting like *hell*... *"Somnus...?"* she mumbled

"Morning,"
She mumbles, standing over her with the cinderblock clutched in her hand.
"I just wanted to say- this isn't personal."
"What are you doing ?..." *what's happening? What is she doing ?... * she was confused, and her vision was still a bit blurry
Somnus lifts the block into the air, then *slams* it down onto Superbia's knee with all the righteous conviction of a knight wielding a holy sword.
Superbia let out a loud and pained scream, *Why?!* was the only question in her mind. Wasn't Somnus her friends ? Friends don't hurt eachother...

"It's not personal,"
She repeats,
"Blame your *partner* for betting with your life."
She brings it down again, wincing sympathetically at the sickening crunch of the blow.
"This is from *Morise."*
She screamed again, tearing up. Why would this happen because of Morise ? *why ?* "Somnus..." She managed to quietly mumble

"I'm sorry,"
She looks down at her, feeling a slight pang of remorse.
"But if Morise insists on being needlessly cruel and dishonest, they need to learn that that has *consequences."*
She slams the block down a final time, then tosses it to the side, panting slightly.
"...Find better friends, Superbia."

She was Just crying now. It was painful, and her head was getting fuzzier. Her stand manifested, and almost punched Somnus, but stopped right before. Superbia couldn't hurt someone she'd consider a friend.

"Take it up with them whenever they find you,"
She mumbles,
*"Confront* them. They need to learn what this feels like."
She steps away again, gives her another lingering glance, then vanishes.

An owl dives in, shifting into Morise as they land on the floor. They're carrying a health pack. "Shit- Superbia, I'm so sorry-" They grab the needle from the pack and ||quickly stab it into her, pressing the plunger all the way down||. "Please be okay, please be okay-"

Superbia was still on the ground. She was speechless. But it looked like she was better. 
Lady Lugubre went by her side and bumbed her head on Superbia's cheek.
They cradle her in their arms, and they aren't feeling too good, muttering "Please be fine-" over and over, and tears stream from their eyes. They haven't cried for billions of years now.

Superbia whispered "I'm... *fine*" She definitly was fine physically, but mentally ? Not so much. She wasn't crying anymore, her face was kind of just...blank. What Somnus had said to her was all she had in her mind

"I'm going to kill her. Her contract was stupidly null, and I thought I could explain that to her. But nooo, she's just gotta...." The tears stop streaming and their spine cracks in several places as they involuntarily shift into their true form. Pretty spooky.
"Do not. I won't let you kill her." She barely reacted to Morise's shift in form, but Lady Lugubre flew on a roof nearby. She Did Not Like The Vibe.
"...Why not?" They grimace and repress that form, shifting back into their main one.
"I still consider her a *friend*. Despite what she has done. And *you* seem to be the reason for her actions"
"....I can take responsibility for that, but I didn't mean for this to happen... I thought it was going to be fine- And she could have been lying to you, you know."
"I don't know *what* happened. But she told me you bet *my* life on something. And I..." She teared up a little "*I think that's terrible if it's the truth*"
"I didn't bet your *life*- I got angry, and Somnus was going to hurt you, and-" They shake their head violently. "I'd never want you to get hurt."
"It's done now. It's over. Whatever happened I don't *want* to know. I-I think I need some time. Alone."
"..." They turn their head away. "If you need to go anywhere, I can drop you off." They say quietly, calmly.
"I'll be fine, My Dearest. You must have many things to do, I will see you around" she gave Morise a slight smile and waved
"...Yeah." They stand up, and teleport out.
